subSubSection.paragraph:
Diagnosis.
Metallic dark blue with turquoise sheen (
Figs 13
, 
47
). Sides of pronotal disc granulate anteriorly, becoming punctate with effaced granules posteriorly. Pronotal disc coarsely rugose (
Figs 13
, 
47
). Posteromedial process of pronotum produced into short denticle, not bifurcated but truncate apically (
Fig. 47
). Anterolateral margins of pronotal disc without ridge or line of tubercles (
Fig. 47
). Posterolateral angles of pronotum much longer than posteromedial process (
Fig. 47
). Elytral striae scabriculous, distinctly impressed, superficially punctate (
Fig. 13
). Elytral interstriae scabriculous, distinctly smooth (except for interstriae VI and VII with lightly roughened integument), superficially punctate, flat (
Fig. 13
).
